    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nReplace hand-written fused kernels for elementwise/reduction patterns with automatic MLIR-based decomposition, subgraph discovery, and Triton kernel generation.\r\n\r\n**Key result:** 75 auto-generated Triton kernels running E2E on Nemotron-3-Nano-30B-A3B-FP8 with coherent output — no hand-written kernels needed.\r\n\r\n### What it does\r\n\r\n1. **Decomposes** high-level ops (RMSNorm) into 15 primitive ops (mul, rsqrt, reduce_mean, etc.) using xDSL pattern rewriter\r\n2. **Discovers** maximal fusible subgraphs via greedy connected-component algorithm\r\n3. **Generates** Triton kernels from subgraph structure (string-based codegen, all f32 compute with downcast at store)\r\n4. **Replaces** subgraph ops in the FX graph with calls to the generated `torch.library.custom_op` kernels\r\n5. **Handles** scalar operands (splat), inline rmsnorm patterns, multi-branch fusion, and dynamic shapes\r\n\r\n### What it replaces\r\n\r\nThe `mlir_fuse_add_rms_norm` transform (hard-coded pattern + FlashInfer/template kernel) is removed. The new `mlir_elementwise_fusion` transform is a superset — it auto-discovers and fuses any elementwise/reduction chain, not just add+rmsnorm.\r\n\r\n### Novel fusion capability\r\n\r\nPatterns like `add + rmsnorm + silu_gate` (which had NO pre-existing kernel) are automatically discovered and fused. Unit tests validate this on GPU with numerical correctness.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n| Component | Files | What |\r\n|-----------|-------|------|\r\n| Primitive dialect | `mlir/dialect.py` | 14 new ops (mul, sub, neg, pow, rsqrt, sqrt, silu, gelu, relu, tanh, reduce_sum, reduce_mean, cast, splat) |\r\n| Decomposition | `mlir/decompose.py`, `mlir/decompose_rules/` | Registry + RMSNorm decomposition rule |\r\n| Subgraph discovery | `mlir/fusion/subgraph_discovery.py` | Greedy algorithm with multi-branch merging + zero-operand pulling |\r\n| Subgraph replacement | `mlir/fusion/subgraph_replace.py` | Replace subgraph ops with fused AdOpaque in MLIR IR |\r\n| Triton codegen | `mlir/codegen/triton_emitter.py` | Emission table, tempfile+importlib compilation, torch custom op registration |\r\n| Kernel cache | `mlir/codegen/kernel_cache.py` | Hash-based dedup by op connectivity + dtypes |\r\n| FX converters | `mlir/fx_to_mlir.py`, `mlir/mlir_to_fx.py` | 9 aten elementwise ops + pow/mean + scalar to splat lowering + all primitive raising |\r\n| Transform | `transform/library/mlir_elementwise_fusion.py` | Full pipeline: FX to MLIR to decompose to discover to codegen to replace to MLIR to FX |\r\n| Config | `config/default.yaml` | `mlir_elementwise_fusion` enabled, `mlir_fuse_add_rms_norm` removed |\r\n| **Removed** | `mlir/patterns/`, `mlir/codegen/templates/`, `mlir_fused_add_rms_norm.py` | Old hard-coded pattern + template kernel + FlashInfer codegen |\r\n\r\n## Test Coverage\r\n\r\n- `test_dialect.py` — 14 primitive op construction + registration (14 tests)\r\n- `test_decompose.py` — RMSNorm decomposition correctness (4 tests)\r\n- `test_subgraph_discovery.py` — Subgraph boundaries, multi-output, reductions (4 tests)\r\n- `test_string_codegen.py` — Generated kernel compilation + GPU numerical correctness (3 tests)\r\n- `test_elementwise_fusion_e2e.py` — Full pipeline, novel fusion (add+rmsnorm+silu_gate), FX roundtrip (7 tests)\r\n- `test_fx_mlir_roundtrip.py` — FX to MLIR to FX with decomposition (5 tests)\r\n- **E2E:** Nemotron-3-Nano-30B-A3B-FP8 — 75/75 subgraphs fused, coherent text generation\r\n\r\nTotal: 37 unit tests (all passing)\r\n\r\n## PR Checklist\r\n\r\n- [x] PR description clearly explains what and why\r\n- [x] Follows TRT-LLM CODING GUIDELINES\r\n- [x] Test cases provided for new code paths\r\n- [x] No new external dependencies (xDSL already a dependency)\r\n- [x] E2E validated on Nemotron Nano 30B FP8\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/issues/12508\r\n## GitHub Bot Help\r\n\r\nTo see a list of available CI bot commands, please comment `/bot help`.\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n## New Features\r\n* Enabled MLIR-based elementwise fusion with automatic Triton kernel generation and in-memory kernel caching\r\n* Added bidirectional FX-MLIR graph conversion support\r\n* Introduced RMSNorm decomposition and primitive operation support\r\n* Extended MLIR dialect with 20+ operations and FP8 type support\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n* Added comprehensive test coverage for MLIR decomposition, fusion discovery, and Triton codegen\r\n\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\nNanov3 fp8 perf:\r\n\r\n```\r\nBefore\r\nmax_concurrency,TPOT avg,user TPS avg,output TPS avg\r\n1,3.4206764178178175,292.3398409715523,287.62983001974277\r\n2,3.9491645993176285,253.21811103360665,494.5599128661371\r\n4,4.943891019438802,202.26983080090494,810.6277006888748\r\n8,5.991833179833875,166.89383198544346,1306.2290672334664\r\n16,8.145305384884688,122.77010532419183,1727.76216947437\r\n32,10.369565217559368,96.43605869864668,3017.6772857076453\r\n64,13.74550225795083,72.75107022164785,4611.555649257188\r\n128,17.83133927244237,56.081037140348755,7077.975946421991\r\n256,23.950796837784626,41.75226430973713,10301.935288097702\r\n\r\n\r\nmlir generated rmsnorm and add rmsnorm fusion\r\nmax_concurrency,TPOT avg,user TPS avg,output TPS avg\r\n1,3.4288033204966495,291.6469410835596,286.80142960896006\r\n2,4.174999914811271,239.52096297113448,472.1874711573047\r\n4,4.883802015592673,204.75850511696984,804.7960377049902\r\n8,5.934020173098525,168.51981807096504,1314.703020097369\r\n16,8.115298004012105,123.22406392292828,1750.773921810975\r\n32,10.695062835258076,93.50108694110067,2960.686087723275\r\n64,13.647257428833077,73.27479570270742,4624.491183043287\r\n128,17.582184806980408,56.87575298395135,7161.500566861907\r\n256,24.215994669835215,41.295020652017875,10291.482253312155\r\n```\r\n<img width=\"2964\" height=\"1764\" alt=\"test\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ea4c1fc2-e363-45b6-b78b-57fe3299a3bc\" />\r\n",
